[49m[38;5;9m- 25    [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Amazon Kinesis Data Streams (or EventBridge) for the engagement event bus.** Delivery receipts from SNS/SES/Connect and appointment outcomes from your scheduling system all need to land in a single stream where the reward computation can consume them. Kinesis works; EventBridge works; which one you pick depends on whether you prefer Kinesis's ordered partitions or EventBridge's rule-based routing. Either way, the principle is the same: one event bus, heterogeneous producers, downstream consumers for reward computation and monitoring.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon Kinesis Data Streams (or EventBridge) for the engagement event bus.** Delivery receipts from SNS/SES/Connect and appointment outcomes from your scheduling system all need to land in a single stream where the reward computation can consume them. Kinesis works; EventBridge works; which one you pick depends on whether you prefer Kinesis's ordered partitions or EventBridge's rule-based routing. Either way, the principle is the same: one event bus, heterogeneous producers, downstream consumers for reward computation and monitoring.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     26[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Portal push notifications: a HIPAA-constrained channel.** If your organization has a patient-facing mobile app with push notifications (via Amazon SNS Mobile Push to APNs/FCM), you can include it as a candidate channel. However, Apple Push Notification service (APNs) and Google Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) are not typically covered under a BAA. This means you cannot send PHI in the push payload itself. The architecture pattern that works: send a content-free notification ("You have a new appointment reminder; tap to view") that triggers the app to fetch the full reminder details from your BAA-covered backend via an authenticated API call. The app renders the details locally after the patient unlocks and authenticates. Delivery events flow back via SNS Mobile Push platform attributes and CloudWatch metrics on the platform application endpoint. This adds latency (the patient must open the app to see details) but keeps PHI within your BAA boundary.
